## Database Schema (Prisma)

```prisma
// prisma/schema.prisma

model User {
  id            String        @id @default(uuid())
  name          String
  email         String        @unique
  phone         String?
  homeCurrency  String        @default("INR")
  fcmToken      String?
  createdAt     DateTime      @default(now())
  groups        GroupMember[]
  paidExpenses  Expense[]     @relation("Payer")
  splits        Split[]
}

model Group {
  id            String        @id @default(uuid())
  name          String
  emoji         String?
  baseCurrency  String        @default("INR")
  createdAt     DateTime      @default(now())
  members       GroupMember[]
  expenses      Expense[]
}

model GroupMember {
  id       String @id @default(uuid())
  user     User   @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])
  userId   String
  group    Group  @relation(fields: [groupId], references: [id])
  groupId  String
  role     String @default("member")    // "admin" | "member"
}

model Expense {
  id            String    @id @default(uuid())
  group         Group     @relation(fields: [groupId], references: [id])
  groupId       String
  description   String
  amount        Float
  currency      String
  amountInBase  Float     // Always stored in INR for balance calculation
  vibeTag       String?   // "food" | "drinks" | "travel" | "fun" | "stay"
  payer         User      @relation("Payer", fields: [payerId], references: [id])
  payerId       String
  splitType     String    @default("equal")  // "equal" | "percentage" | "exact" | "itemized"
  isRecurring   Boolean   @default(false)
  recurringDay  Int?      // Day of month (1-28) for auto-log
  receiptUrl    String?   // Firebase Storage URL of scanned receipt image
  createdAt     DateTime  @default(now())
  splits        Split[]
}

model Split {
  id          String    @id @default(uuid())
  expense     Expense   @relation(fields: [expenseId], references: [id])
  expenseId   String
  user        User      @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])
  userId      String
  amount      Float     // Share amount in INR
  percentage  Float?    // Only populated for percentage splits
  settled     Boolean   @default(false)
  settledAt   DateTime?
}

model Settlement {
  id          String   @id @default(uuid())
  groupId     String
  fromUserId  String
  toUserId    String
  amount      Float
  currency    String
  settledAt   DateTime @default(now())
}

model CurrencyRate {
  id        String   @id @default(uuid())
  base      String   // e.g. "INR"
  target    String   // e.g. "USD"
  rate      Float
  updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt
}
```

---

## API Endpoints

```
AUTH
  POST  /api/auth/login                    Verify Firebase token, return user profile
  POST  /api/auth/register                 Create new user in DB

GROUPS
  GET   /api/groups                        All groups for logged-in user
  POST  /api/groups                        Create a new group
  GET   /api/groups/:id                    Single group with members + stats
  PUT   /api/groups/:id                    Update group name / currency
  DELETE /api/groups/:id                   Delete group
  POST  /api/groups/:id/members            Add member by email or phone
  DELETE /api/groups/:id/members/:userId   Remove member

EXPENSES
  GET   /api/expenses?groupId=             All expenses for a group
  POST  /api/expenses                      Add new expense
  PUT   /api/expenses/:id                  Edit expense
  DELETE /api/expenses/:id                 Delete expense

BALANCES
  GET   /api/balances?groupId=             Simplified settlement list for group
  POST  /api/balances/settle               Mark a debt as paid

CURRENCY
  GET   /api/currency/rates?base=INR       All exchange rates for a base currency
  GET   /api/currency/convert?from=INR&to=USD&amount=5000

RECEIPT
  POST  /api/receipt/scan                  Upload image → returns extracted item list

NUDGE
  POST  /api/nudge/send
        body: { toUserId, groupId, tone: "gentle" | "firm" | "savage" }
```

---

## Utility Logic Explained

### Debt Simplification Algorithm
```
File: utils/debtSimplifier.js  (used in both client and server)

Step 1 — Calculate net balance per person:
  netBalance = totalAmountTheyPaid - totalAmountOwed

Step 2 — Split into two lists:
  creditors = people with positive net (others owe them)
  debtors   = people with negative net (they owe others)

Step 3 — Greedily match largest debtor with largest creditor:
  While any debt remains:
    take biggest debtor (owes the most)
    take biggest creditor (is owed the most)
    settlement = min(|debtor|, creditor)
    record: debtor pays creditor that amount
    reduce both balances by settlement

Result: minimum number of bank transfers to clear all debts
```

### Currency Conversion Flow
```
File: client/src/utils/currencyUtils.js

convert(amount, fromCurrency, toCurrency, rates)
  1. toBase: amount × rates[fromCurrency]  → gives INR amount
  2. fromBase: inrAmount / rates[toCurrency] → gives target amount

fmt(amount, currencyCode)
  → "₹5,000.00" | "$59.88" | "¥664" (JPY has no decimals)

Rate refresh (server):
  jobs/currencyRefresh.job.js runs every 60 minutes
  → hits ExchangeRate-API with base=INR
  → upserts all rates into CurrencyRate table
  → client fetches fresh rates on app load via GET /api/currency/rates
```

### Spending Personality Engine
```
File: client/src/utils/personalityEngine.js

Input:  all splits for a user in a group, each with a vibeTag
Output: { label, emoji, topCategory, topPercent, totalSpent }

Logic:
  tally spend per tag → find highest % category → map to label

Labels:
  food   > 40%  →  "The Foodie"         🍕
  drinks > 35%  →  "The Party Starter"  🍺
  travel > 40%  →  "The Uber Caller"    🚗
  fun    > 40%  →  "The Adventurer"     🎡
  stay   > 40%  →  "Comfort King/Queen" 🛏
  mixed         →  "The Balanced One"   ⚖️
```

### Nudge Message Templates
```
File: client/src/constants/nudgeTones.js

gentle:  "Hey {name}! Just a friendly reminder — you owe {amount}. No rush 😊"
firm:    "Hi {name}, please settle your share of {amount} when you can."
savage:  "{name}. {amount}. Still waiting. You know who you are. 👀"
```

---

## Feature Summary

| Feature | Key Files | How It Works |
|---|---|---|
| Multi-currency converter | `CurrencyConverter.jsx`, `currencyService.js`, `currencyUtils.js` | User picks amount + currency → converted to all others using cached rates |
| Group expense split | `ExpenseForm.jsx`, `SplitTypeSelector.jsx`, `splitUtils.js` | 4 split modes; all amounts stored in INR in DB |
| AI receipt scanner | `ReceiptScanner.jsx`, `receipt.service.js` (server) | Photo → GPT-4o Vision → JSON items → assign to members |
| Debt simplification | `debtSimplifier.js`, `balance.service.js` | Graph algorithm minimizes number of payments |
| Spending personality | `personalityEngine.js`, `SpendingPersonality.jsx` | Tallies spend per tag, maps to fun label |
| Nudge system | `NudgeButton.jsx`, `nudge.service.js` | Pick tone → FCM push notification sent |
| Spin-to-pay | `SpinWheel.jsx` | CSS animation wheel, random member selected |
| Recurring expenses | `RecurringToggle.jsx`, `recurringExpense.job.js` | Daily cron auto-logs expenses on set day of month |
| Timeline view | `TimelineView.jsx`, `dateUtils.js` | Expenses grouped by date in vertical scroll |

